channel.description:
I was observing some code and I saw this:
[code=java] /** * The constructor I use this for things that can not be static that have to * be ran for the server * * @throws InterruptedException * if the thread is interrupted */ public Server() throws InterruptedException {
/** * Turns on the event manager used to run tasks that may need to be ran * in the future or at a different time in mills */ this.eventManager = new EventManager();
/** * Starts the eventmanager thread */ runThread("EventManager", eventManager);
/** * Sends a message that the eventmanager is successfully started */ Logger.log(this, "Eventmanager is successfully running...");
/** * Sleeps the thread */ Thread.sleep(500);
} [/code]
Why do you need to sleep the thread?
Thanks, Arham
EDIT: Found out why. Just for the sake of learning, I'll post it so other people can see.
[code=java] * Lets sleep a little, limiting the amount of * connections that can be accepted. This will * stop a possible huge flood of people connecting * at once, which may cause problems. */ Thread.sleep(100); [/code]
